OL,7,Froom with trans colleague no clearer
OL,8,Fafter Supreme Court ruling
OL,10,FThe day surgery unit band five nurse,
OL,11,Fwho has worked for the trust since
OL,12,F2002, added: "I was initially
OL,13,Fapprehensive about expressing my
OL,14,Fconcerns due to a fear of being
OL,15,Flabelled a bigot or transphobic.
OL,17,F"Someone had obviously allowed RH to
OL,18,Fbe in our changing room. I thought
OL,19,Fthat if I spoke up about it, it would
OL,20,Fbe seen as offensive.
OL,26,@tD@NOUyD@AOU
